    h2 Radio Layout
    p Radio layout is pretty simple:
    :code(lang="html")
          <!-- radio element -->
          <label class="radio">
            <!-- radio input -->
            <input type="radio">
            <!-- radio icon -->
            <i class="icon-radio"></i>
          </label>
    h2 Radio Group/List
    p To create Radio group/list we need to use <a href="list-view.html">List View</a> with few additions:
    :code(lang="html")
          <div class="list">
            <ul>
              <!-- Single radio item -->
              <li>
                <label class="item-radio item-content">
                  <!-- Radio input -->
                  <input type="radio" name="my-radio" value="radio-1"/>
                  <!-- Radio icon -->
                  <i class="icon icon-radio"></i>
                  <div class="item-inner">
                    <!-- Radio Title -->
                    <div class="item-title">Books</div>
                  </div>
                </label>
              </li>
              <!-- Another radio item -->
              <li>
                <label class="item-radio item-content">
                  <!-- Checked by default -->
                  <input type="radio" name="my-radio" value="radio-2" checked/>
                  <i class="icon icon-radio"></i>
                  <div class="item-inner">
                    <div class="item-title">Music</div>
                  </div>
                </label>
              </li>
              ...
            </ul>
          </div>
    .important-note
      ul
        li <code>item-content</code> must be a <code><b>&lt;label&gt;</b></code> element with additional <code><b>item-radio</b></code> class
        li Radio input (<code>&lt;input type="radio"&gt;</code>) must be a first child of <code>item-content</code>
        li Radio icon must be <b>after</b> radio input
